** Who is R6 Digital anyway? **

R6 Digital helps businesses thrive online. We’re a team of passionate
creatives, designers, developers and marketers who enjoy creating compelling
digital experiences and marketing campaigns for our customers across
Australasia, the US and the UK.

We’re a rapidly growing digital agency and custom software house looking for
an enthusiastic, organised and proactive Accountant to join us in our Brisbane
CBD office. You’ll be joining a great team of talented marketers, designers,
and developers with a fun team culture where we genuinely enjoy coming to work
every day and work-life balance is a reality.

** The Role **

Reporting directly to the CFO, the ** Accountant ** plays a critical role in
the financial and management accounting functions of R6 Digital. The
Accountant will assist in all aspects of the company’s finances, ensuring that
the executive team has timely financial information to facilitate decision
making.

** As an Accountant, some of your responsibilities will include: **

  * Transactional accounting, including daily _ reconciliations _ in Xero of expenditure and receipting of payments; 
  * Full function _ Accounts Payable _ , including international payments; 
  * Full function _ Accounts Receivable _ , including raising invoices, receipting payments, and following up delinquent accounts; 
  * Active _ expense management _ , including audits of subscriptions and recurring expenses; 
  * Assistance in the preparation of _ monthly reporting _ (including profit and loss reporting, balance sheet, cash flow reporting, forecast reporting) for the company directors, including commentary and advice to aid decision making; 
  * Assistance in the regular _ budgeting, forecasting and scenario planning _ to assist with company goal execution; 
  * Daily and weekly monitoring and management of operating _ cash flows _ and regular cash flow forecasting; 
  * Assistance in the _ full end of month process, _ including reconciliations of all balance sheet accounts, and journal entries for accruals, prepayments, and revenue recognition; 
  * Preparation and lodgement of _ activity statements _ with the ATO and _ payroll tax return _ with the Office of State Revenue; 
  * Working with the CFO, external R&D consultants and internal development team, preparation and lodgement of annual Research and Development tax incentive; 
  * Research and execution of _ financial grants _ suitable for the company, including working with the CFO for the Export Market Development Grant (EMDG) applications and reporting; 
  * Assist the CFO and Executive Team with ad hoc _ strategic financial planning _ and special projects, as needed.   

** The ideal person for this role will have: **

  * _ Tertiary qualification _ in Accounting, Finance or Commerce; 
  * _ CPA or CA qualification, _ or actively working towards, will be highly regarded; 
  * Minimum of 2-3 years financial and management _ accounting experience _ ; 
  * Strong knowledge and use of _ Microsoft Excel _ ; 
  * Experience using _ Xero _ will be highly regarded; 
  * Strong _ attention to detail _ with dedication to accuracy and well-developed _ organisational skills _ ; 
  * The ability to _ problem solve, prioritise and meet deadlines _ in a fast working and continually changing agile agency environment; 
  * A high degree of _ professionalism and appreciation for confidentiality _ ; 
  * Excellent _ written and verbal communication skills _ that enable you to communicate with clients and stakeholders over the phone or by email; 
  * Previous experience within a digital agency, technology or marketing environment will be highly regarded. 

** Why would you want to work for R6 Digital? **

  * Honestly – the team! An amazing group of people who love to have fun, love a good joke and enjoy our time together – all while working hard together to deliver fantastic results for our clients. 
  * We also have Friday avo bevs and game sessions (Xbox to CS:GO to Board Games to table tennis) as well as other regular fun activities. 
  * While we are office based, we genuinely value and encourage a healthy work/life balance and don't expect you to work overtime all the time. 

If you enjoy variety and the dynamics of an active team environment and would
take pride in making a positive contribution to a rapidly growing Digital
Agency and Software Company, this could be the opportunity you’ve been looking
for.

Your application should include a current CV and cover letter outlining your
